==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resorb
<hw>Re*sorb"</hw> <pr>(r?-s?rb")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>reorbere</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>sorbere</ets> to
suck or drink in.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To swallow up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now lifted by the tide, and now <qex>resorbed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>to absorb (something which has
been secreted or exuded by the same organism).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resorbent</ent>⟦br⟧
